OL,3,C'We can't thank them enough': Margaret
OL,4,CLoughlin's SS Vega memories 80 years on
OL,6,FBy the Winter of 1944, supplies to the
OL,7,Fisland had nearly stopped and people
OL,8,Fwere starving.
OL,10,FMargaret says: "My mother used to cry
OL,11,Fbecause she didn't have food to give
OL,12,Fus - it was awful.
OL,14,F"We'd try and get vegetables or
OL,15,Fsomething from somebody but it was
OL,16,Fhard (...) we didn't have a big garden
OL,17,Fat the back - you couldn't grow
OL,18,Fanything - so what do you do?"
