OL,3,C'We can't thank them enough': Margaret
OL,4,CLoughlin's SS Vega memories 80 years on
OL,6,FDespite having very little during the
OL,7,Fyears of Occupation, Margaret
OL,8,Fremembers islanders sharing what they
OL,9,Fdid have to help others.
OL,11,FShe explains: "We used to get some
OL,12,Fsugar beet syrup from Mr Daghorn, and
OL,13,Fhe used to make sugar beet syrup. That
OL,14,Fwas like a gift - it was lovely -
OL,15,Fsomething that we never had before."
OL,17,FFollowing the harshest few months of
OL,18,Fthe Occupation, the arrival of the SS
OL,19,FVega spread hope and joy.
