OL,3,C'We can't thank them enough': Margaret
OL,4,CLoughlin's SS Vega memories 80 years on
OL,6,FAnd the parcels from New Zealand held:
OL,8,FEach parcel weighed around 10.5kg and
OL,9,Fwas expected to feed someone for about
OL,10,Fa month.
OL,12,FMargaret describes: "You had the Klim
OL,13,F(powdered milk), the sugar, the tea -
OL,14,Fall the different things in there -
OL,15,Fthe jam, marmalade - it was wonderful."
OL,17,FMore than 80 years after Margaret
OL,18,Freceived her Red Cross parcel that
OL,19,Fsense of gratitude still exists today.
